Fundamentals of AIML

Cardio Good Fitness Project

Objective¶

The Cardio Good Fitness is a retail store which sells various products of treadmills to customers. The store caters to the needs of different categories of customers. The dataset derived has different attributes which provides an insight on the buying patterns of customer. The store would like to understand the pattern of the purchaase of treadmills across different age groups, Gender specific, Marital status , Fitness quotient and many more. The data will provide an insight to the store in customizing their offerings to the end customers

Let us first import the necessary libraries before starting our analysis.

Importing the libraries¶

In [2]:
# Libraries to help with reading and manipulating data

Let us now load the dataset.

Loading the dataset¶

In [3]:
# read the dataset
url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Seprishi/CardioGoodFitnessProject/main/CardioGoodFitness.csv'
data = pd.read_csv(url, index_col=0)

Overview of the dataset¶

DataSet Details¶

The dataset consists of the following features:

  1. Product - The model no. of the treadmill
  2. Age - Age of the customer in no of years
  3. Gender - Gender of the customer
  4. Education - Education of the customer in no. of years
  5. Marital Status - Marital status of the customer
  6. Usage - Avg. # times the customer wants to use the treadmill every week
  7. Fitness - Self rated fitness score of the customer (5 - very fit, 1 - very unfit)
  8. Income - Income of the customer
  9. Miles- Miles that a customer expects to run

Outlier Treatment¶

From the plots, we can infer that there are many outliers for the Income and Miles columns and hence, this needs treatment

In [23]:
Outliertreateddata = data.copy()
In [29]:
#Outlier Treatment: Remove top 5% & bottom 1% of the Column Outlier values
Q3 = Outliertreateddata['Income'].quantile(0.75)
Q1 = Outliertreateddata['Income'].quantile(0.25)
IQR = Q3-Q1
Outliertreateddata = Outliertreateddata[(Outliertreateddata['Income'] > Q1 - 1.5*IQR) & (Outliertreateddata['Income'] < Q3 + 1.6*IQR)]

Q3 = Outliertreateddata['Miles'].quantile(0.75)
Q1 = Outliertreateddata['Miles'].quantile(0.25)
IQR = Q3-Q1
Outliertreateddata = Outliertreateddata[(Outliertreateddata['Miles'] > Q1 - 1.5*IQR) & (Outliertreateddata['Miles'] < Q3 + 1.5*IQR)]

Observations¶

TM195

  • Minimum age of the customers is 18 and the maximum is 47
  • Used minimum 2 days/week and maximum 5 days/week on an average
  • Minimum miles run/week is 48 and maximum is 140, with outliers ranging until 200 miles/week
  • Average fitness rating of the customers is 3
  • Minimum average annual income is 30k and the maximum is 68k
  • very few outliers

TM498

  • Minimum age of the customers is 19 and the maximum is 45
  • No explicit minimum and maximum days/week
  • Minimum miles run/week is 48 and maximum is 140, with outliers ranging until 200 miles/week
  • Average fitness rating of the customers is 3
  • Minimum average annual income is 32k and the maximum is 67k with very litte outliers on both sides

TM798

  • Minimum age of the customers is 22 and the maximum is 38
  • Used minimum 3 days/week and maximum 6 days/week
  • Minimum miles run/week is 80 and maximum is 300, with outliers until about 360 miles/week
  • Minimum fitness rating is 3
  • Minimum average annual income is 48k and the maximum is 104k IQR between 58k-91k

Usage vs Marital Status Vs Gender

  • Average usage/week has significantly same values for the minimum usage/week which is 2 and maximum usage/week which is 5

Category - Teens, Youngsters, Above30s and Middleaged

AgeRange - 14-20 , 20-30, 30-40 & 40-60

  • Added 1 new categorial feature based on the income

IncomeRange - Low Income, Middle income, Moderate income and High income

data['Category'] = pd.cut(data['Age'], bins,labels=labels)

bins_income = [29000, 35000, 60000, 85000,105000]
labels_income = ['Low Income','Middle income','Moderate income', 'High income']
data['IncomeRange'] = pd.cut(data['Income'],bins_income,labels = labels_income)

Conclusions and Recommendations¶

Key Insights¶

Insight on Customers¶

  • Partnered Customers are having the treadmills more than the Single customers
  • 57.8% of Males and 42.2% of Females are using the Treadmills
  • Marital status does not influence the average usage/week.
  • TM195 and TM498 are purchased by Teens and none of the TM798 is purchased by the teens
  • Males are generally active on all age groups. However in Teens Group, Females are generally more active
  • TM798 model is not affordable for the Low Income group
  • TM798 model is bought by both male and female customers who are very fit
  • Youngsters are generally very active and have high fitness scores
  • Fitness scores of 2,3 and 4 are seen in 28 year old females on average
  • Usage and miles run per week by customers have a strong correlation and determines their fitness level
  • Age and Income of customers have a positive correlation
  • Average Age of Customers using Treadmill is 28.78
  • The Age group of customers using the Treadmill is 18 - 50 and 75 percentage of them are 33 or under.
  • The Education levels of the users are between 12-21 and average being 15.57
  • The Average usage of the treadmill every week by the customers are 3.3 days. 50% of the customers are using the treadmill for 3 times and Max being 7 times in a week
  • The income range of customers buying treadmill starts at 29K and Maximum income of 100K. Average income is approximately 54K
  • Customers are running an average of 103.19 Miles per week on the treadmill
  • The customers with more than 70K are running more ranging between 120-300 miles. Customers with income less than 70 K are running less ranging between 30-150 miles mostly with few reaching 200 Miles
  • More usage of the treadmills lead to the high fitness scores
  • Customers using TM798 model are covering more miles per week, Very Fit and more educated compared to the users using other models
  • Partnered customers are using TM798 and ran more miles than single customers comparatively
  • The income of Single customers are less than 70K only with few exceptions

Insights on Products used by Customers¶

TM195

  • The Most sold product and ageneral purpose treadmill for all the user age groups.It can be marketed as a base product for the customers who get in to fitness regime in the beginner level.This model suits for the younger Population and customers with a limited usage of 3 or 4 times in a week

TM498

  • The TM498 model is similar to TM195 and has the same characteristics. Both Models can go together for the users who fall in the average usage category. Also, this model is suitable for the users with an income of less than 70K

TM798

  • TM798 is the high end model with great specification which generates interest to the fitness freaks. TM798 is mostly the premium treadmill product of the company. Customers using this model are highly fit as they posses a good fitness score and covered more miles per week than any other customers using other models. The customers are highly educated and belonging to the high income group. Primarily, this model is bought by the Male customers.

Business Recommendations¶

  • The offerings from the retail store caters to the needs of the customers ranging from Low to high income groups spanning across ages and with different fitness interests

  • The models TM195 and TM498 primarily caters to the beginners and an affordable product to cater the moderate usage needs

  • To increase the sales of the premium product TM798, the store focusses on attracting the teens, younger community to buy it as they are not using it.

  • Brand the TM 798 as a model used by Athletes to promote the sales among the teens.

  • Recommendations for the higher income group with good education levels is to use the premium model TM798

  • The campaign to be created for the different age groups addressing the needs so that all the 3 models can be used by different age groups

  • Partnered Customers are more than the Single customers. Using right advertisement, more families/partners can be made aware on the fitness needs and the usage of the Treadmills

  • Singles above 40 years can be recommended with the higher end product(TM798) as they wish to run more miles and therefore the usage would be higher.

  • Create an exclusive offering for the income group between 50-70K with EMI plans so that they can be recommended to buy the premium product of the company.

  • TM798 to be recommended for Partnered males with a higher income

  • Investigate on why the female customers are no prefering the Model TM798 and take corrective actions such as Offers, Incentives, special campaigns to promote awareness on products etc. to increase the sales among females

  • Considering above observations, We can attract customers to upgrade from their existing treadmill and switch to TM798 ,highlighting extra features this Treadmill provides.
